tip.text: Fish burrito is gigantic and delicious. Great after a long hike or surf session. Pair it with the green tomatillo salsa 👌🏻
Interesting rock formation that's nice around sunset. Locals use it for fishing. Good for a quick photo op.
Brunch is delicious and a good value at $25. Make a reservation on OpenTable ahead of time to secure your spot. Evenings are more low key.
The cheapest, most delicious date spot around 👨🏻‍💼🍔🍟👩🏻‍💼
The entire tasting takes about 3 hours - 3 hours of food heaven. Pair it with a tequila based cocktail and then just 😄😌🤤
If there's a line, sit at the outside bar area for immediate food and drink service. The breakfast croissant is a must try 👌🏻
Not only are the views amazing but the space is clean and the staff is courteous and efficient. I agree that it's the best Taco Bell around.
Whatever you order, Dave space for the hula pie, a Duke's specialty.
Burgers are tasty, huge and should def be split. Pair with a local Tahoe brew

formattedAddress: El Camino Del Mar (at Point Lobos Ave)

tip.text: Best diner views in SF. Breakfast is the time to go. Expect a little wait if you want a booth.
Hang by the fireplace in the lobby for toasty marina views 🔥🚢
Trendy styling and convenient weekend hours. Don't be scared by the ambience as it's mostly dads that get their haircut here. Quality cuts regardless 👌🏻
Well curated beer list and bar food options. The Bratwurst & Bread is good for a snack or a meal and at $7 it's definitely a steal 👌
Southern cooking and decor. Great for brunch. Grits are delicious and seldom seen 'round these parts.
They've just added a burger that is a delicious blend of meat and peppers. Stacked with caramelized onions and arugula. Well worth a try 👌🏻🍔
Make the rounds first to see what looks good. One of my faves is the roasted pork sandwich w peppers, greens and provolone ( don't remember the name but follow your nose!) Top it off w icecream 👍🏻
Watch boutique with access to the L.U.C Chopard line of haute horologie. Friendly and knowledgable staff.
Great for outdoor brunch. Eggs Benedict are life.
Feels more like a museum than a store. Friendly staff and comfy couches for you to relax and play with all the wrist toys
Giant sized nachos for you and he whole crew. TVs throughout the bar and individual screens at the booths. Michigan and Boston bar
Pana to San Pedro or San Juan takes about 45 minutes. A private boat will run about $30 USD. Waves can get rough later in the day.
Breakfast reigns supreme here. The pancakes are the real stand out. Eggs, home fries, etc are standard diner quality.
Mini bowling, pool, ping pong, air hockey, arcade basketball - everything a drinking aged kid could want
Solid Monte Christo but unless you are in the mood for something very indulgent, the Reuben is a better choice.
The food is excellent and you really can't go wrong. Whatever you order make sure you end with the churros - best churros ever 🙌🏻

formattedAddress: 35 E 21st St (btwn Broadway & Park Ave S)
35 E 21st St (btwn Broadway & Park Ave S)

tip.text: Start by getting a flower in our hair and some holy water on your head. Then head to the left side where there are much less crowds and killer views

venue.name: Tanah Lot Temple (Pura Luhur Tanah Lot)

tip.text: You would not expect some of the tastiest pizza ever to be made in Bali, but believe it! Get the curry pizza and the pizza chocolate to top it off 🍕👌🏻
Coffee of this quality needs to be prepared correctly. Get a medium dark Bali roast made in an aeropress, no milk. The best cup I've ever had!
I love burgers and this place is no exception. The real stand out is the burger salad - looks like a salad, eats like a burger. Get the bison pesto.
The burger is excellent. The quality of the meat is noticeable. Pair with a cab or pinot for optimal enjoyment 😍🍔
Famous for being the restaurant of Anthony Bourdain. The hamburger game is strong and the ambience is what you would expect from a bistro aka white tablecloth vibes

formattedAddress: 411 Park Ave S (btwn E 28th & E 29th St)

tip.text: Have to try the BLT. The lobster is also delicious and very well priced.
6 beer flight is a great value and you get to keep the cup. You can even BYO food too. Closes at 8pm.
Large and delicious lobster roll. A meal in and of itself. Chowders are also good tho skimpy on the clam.

formattedAddress: 770 Franklin Ave (btw Lincoln & St. Johns Pl.)

tip.text: The Scorpion Tiki comes in a sweet tiki cup - great to match your Hawaiian party shirt. Free wifi and lounge area up top
Beautiful back patio for an intimate get together. Get the arugula salad but be careful with the love potion kombucha as your night could take an unexpected turn...
Beautiful lobby in the downtown beach area of Busan. Great breakfast on top floor. Pay for gym and spa access.
The walkway opposite the crossing from Starbucks is also a great place to view the masses

formattedAddress: 道玄坂2/宇田川町/神南1 (井の頭通り)

venue.name: Shibuya Crossing (渋谷駅前スクランブル交差点)

tip.text: Near midtown & in Roppongi, the Grand Hyatt is great for business and leisure. Views of Tokyo Tower and an amazing spa for guests

venue.name: Grand Hyatt Tokyo (グランド ハイアット 東京)
The Ritz-Carlton Tokyo (ザ・リッツ・カールトン東京)

tip.text: Nicest beach in Abu Dhabi but also the priciest. AED 315 (about $85) to access the beach and pool area
Very crowded but big enough to fit all the tourists that visit daily. Beautiful at sunset.

venue.name: Sheikh Zayed Grand Mosque (مسجد الشيخ زايد)
Abu Dhabi International Airport (AUH) (مطار أبو ظبي الدولي)

tip.text: Free wine tasting bar featuring Napa's best. Must try the Darioush which is limited in production
Very bland food cooked for a very large audience. Show is 1 hour long and kind of a snooze fest

location.address: 135A Nam Ky Khoi Nghia St., Dist. 1
formattedAddress: 135A Nam Ky Khoi Nghia St., Dist. 1

tip.text: Awesome day party with DJ and entertainers. Very affordable bottle service. Great place to work off a hangover
An airport lounge with delicious coffee! Skip all the other lounges, this has gourmet eats, drinks and hi-speed wifi

formattedAddress: Dallas/Fort Worth International Airport (Terminal D (opposite gate D17))

venue.name: The Centurion Lounge by American Express

tip.text: Trendy steak/BBQ place with a burger that had me like whoaaaaaaa - also the cauliflower steak is a good appetizer
